Gulf Stocks: Abu Dhabi’s Aldar Properties and Oman’s Bank Sohar

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-02-28T14:25:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/gulf-stocks-abu-dhabi-s-aldar-properties-and-oman-s-bank-sohar.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index  slumped
3.8 percent to the lowest since June 2004, bringing the loss for
the month to 8.1 percent. Oman’s MSM30 Index tumbled 4.9
percent, the most since January 2009, and Saudi Arabia’s measure
slipped 0.2 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Gulf. Symbols are
in parentheses.        Aldar Properties PJSC  (ALDAR UH) slumped to the lowest on
record, retreating 7.2 percent to 1.42 dirhams. Shareholders of
Abu Dhabi’s biggest developer approved the sale of convertible
bonds to Mubadala Development Co.        Bank Sohar  (BKSB OM): The Omani lender tumbled the most in
more than two years, plunging 8.6 percent to 0.159 rial.
Hundreds of protesters, many unemployed Omanis, gathered for a
sit-in for a second day in Sohar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
